This is a collection of routines for quality-aware alignment of Roche/454 reads,
for use either from C or from Python 3 (including a Python 3 C extension).
Functions with asw_* prefix implement asymmetric Smith- Waterman-like algorithm
with inverse scores (URL: http://dx.doi.org/10.1101/gr.6468307)
 

How to install:

 python3 setup.py build
 sudo python3 setup.py install

On Mac OS X, if one does not wish to create a PPC binary:

env CFLAGS="-std=c99" ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386 -arch x86_64" python3 setup.py build
sudo env CFLAGS="-std=c99" ARCHFLAGS="-arch i386 -arch x86_64" python3 setup.py install

To change compiler options, find the Makefile corresponding to your
Python installation. On my Mac OS X Snow Leopard, the Makefile for the
Python 3 installation is at:

/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/3.1/lib/python3.1/config/Makefile
